postgresql instructions:

psql -l -- lists all databases running in postgresql

-- localhost/adminer # this is where i have ubuntu running adminer (after performing various rites of black magic with Apache)

-- use \? within the psql shell to get more help

-- (when running psql) \du will list the users

-- \l will list all databases

\connect <database> -- to start running commands on a specific database

\dt -- list all the tables in the current selected database

\i <sql command file> -- run this command file...

\c postgres -- to connect to some other database...

createdb <NOME_DO_BD> # creates a new database

-- check this out
https://www.tutorialspoint.com/postgresql/postgresql_create_database.htm

postgresql runs on port 5432 by default.

-- get general information with this query
select *
from pgadmin

